    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> rice vinegar </strong>with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> in a medium sized bowl</p><p>Peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Add the <strong>carrot ribbons</strong> to the vinegar mixture and give it all a good old mix up and set aside - this is your <strong>quick-pickled carrot salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-pak-choi/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-pak-choi/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5 min until starting to brown and crisp, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-pak-choi/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is cooking, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> </strong>then trim and slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Wash then cut your <strong>pak choi</strong> in half, separating the <strong>white base</strong> and <strong>green tops</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop the <strong>white base </strong>into bite-size pieces & shred the <strong>green tops</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-pak-choi/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has browned, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>and <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>with the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>ketjap manis </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 2 min further or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once cooked, transfer everything to a bowl and set aside and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-pak-choi/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan (no need to wash it!) to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>white pak choi</strong> (keep the shredded green tops for later) and the <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min, then add the <strong>green tops</strong>, cover and cook for 1-2 min further or until wilted</p><p>Transfer the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pak choi</strong> to a separate bowl</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-pak-choi/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan (no need to wash it!) to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>black</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong> then crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into the pan, over the sesame seeds</p><p>Cook, covered for 2-3 min or until done to your liking \u2013 these are your <strong>sesame fried egg</strong></p><p>Tip: Give your egg a little shake before you crack for perfectly centred yolk!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-pak-choi/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, add the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong> to a bowl then add the <strong>crispy lean pork</strong>, <strong>quick-pickled carrot salad</strong> and <strong>pak choi</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>sesame</strong> <strong>fried egg</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
